					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Four slabs setup at the entrance of the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇadēvarāya 1521 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is highly damaged. It states that Krishnadēvaraya, after his conquest of Raichūru, Alaṁpūru, Mānve, Hānumagalu and Māgaḍe forts Visited Kāḍalūru at the confluence of the Kṛishṇa and Bhimārathi and made a grant of the village Chikalparvi in Mānuve-sīme to god Tiruveṅgaḷanātha while performing <hi rend="italic">ratna-dhēnu, gōsahasra</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kanakāśva mahādānas</hi> in association with his queens Chinnādēvi and Tirumaladēvi. Gods Virūpāksha-dēva, Kālahāstikēśvara and Sangamēśa are mentioned in the record.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1443 Vṛisha, Śrāvaṇa śu 12. Monday corresponding to 1521 A.D., July 16, Tuesday.</p>						

						</summary>
